Hidden (or invisible or transparent) notes can be useful in
preparing theory or composition exercises.

@lilypond[verbatim,quote,relative=2]
c4 d
\hideNotes
e4 f
\unHideNotes
g a
\hideNotes
b
\unHideNotes
c
@end lilypond

Notation objects which are attached to invisible notes are still
visible.

@lilypond[verbatim,quote,relative=2]
c4( d)
\hideNotes
e4(\p f)--
@end lilypond


